    /* This program parses out [weight=exp] from a command. Syntax _parsewt "allowed_weight_types" `0' Example _parsewt "fw aw" `0' Returns s(newcmd) = command with [weight=exp] removed s(weight) = [= ] or nothing
    23 [+] version 6.0 , missing 
    • /*
   This program parses out [weight=exp] from a command.
   Syntax
		_parsewt "allowed_weight_types" `0'
   Example
		_parsewt "fw aw" `0'
   Returns
		s(newcmd) = command with [weight=exp] removed
		s(weight) = [= ]    or   nothing

   Notes:
        1.  Program looks for weights in usual places.  In particular, it
            does not look inside expressions or options.
	2.  Program will use message (frequency weights assumed)", etc.
	3.   in s(weight) is spelled out, equal sign hard against,
	    one blank, followed by expression.
        4.  _parsewt returns s(newcmd) AS IS (`0') if no weights.
        5.  _parsewt returns s(newcmd) with all quotes changed to
            compound quotes if weights were specified.
*/
	version 6.0, missing

program define _parsewt, sclass
    All properties 
    key content

    /* This program parses out [weight=exp] from a command. Syntax _parsewt "allowed_weight_types" command_stuff Example _parsewt "fweight aweight" `*' Returns s(newcmd) = command with [weight=exp] removed s(weight) = "[weight=exp]"
    141 [+] version 6.0 
    • /*
   This program parses out [weight=exp] from a command.
   Syntax
		_parsewt "allowed_weight_types" command_stuff
   Example
		_parsewt "fweight aweight" `*'
   Returns
		s(newcmd) = command with [weight=exp] removed
		s(weight) = "[weight=exp]"

   Note: If there are weights, command must be less than 80 characters.
         If there are no weights, this limit does not apply.

   Note: Program will issue the message "(frequency weights assumed)", etc.,
   if appropriate.
*/
	version 6.0

      *! version 2.0.3  23sep2004
program define _parsewt, sclass
/*
   This program parses out [weight=exp] from a command.
   Syntax
		_parsewt "allowed_weight_types" `0'
   Example
		_parsewt "fw aw" `0'
   Returns
		s(newcmd) = command with [weight=exp] removed
		s(weight) = [= ]    or   nothing

   Notes:
        1.  Program looks for weights in usual places.  In particular, it
            does not look inside expressions or options.
	2.  Program will use message (frequency weights assumed)", etc.
	3.   in s(weight) is spelled out, equal sign hard against,
	    one blank, followed by expression.
        4.  _parsewt returns s(newcmd) AS IS (`0') if no weights.
        5.  _parsewt returns s(newcmd) with all quotes changed to
            compound quotes if weights were specified.
*/
	version 6.0, missing
	sret clear

	gettoken wtypes 0 : 0
	sret local newcmd `"`0'"'
	
	local np 0
	local inopt 0
	while 1 {
		gettoken first 0 : 0, parse(`""[](),"') quotes
		if `"`first'"'=="" {
			exit
		}
		if `np'==0 & `inopt'==0 & `"`first'"'=="[" {
			Parse "`wtypes'" `0'
			if "`s(done)'"=="1" {
				sret local done
				sret local newcmd `"`lhs'`s(rest)'"'
				sret local rest
				exit
			}
			local np = `np' + 1
			local lhs `"`lhs'`first'"'
		}
		else {
			if `"`first'"'=="(" {
				local np = `np' + 1
			}
			else if `"`first'"'==")" { 
				local np = `np' - 1 
			}
			else if `"`first'"'=="," { 
				local inopt  = ~`inopt'
			}
			local lhs `"`lhs'`first'"'
		}
	}
	/*NOTREACHED*/
end

program define Parse, sclass
	sret local done 
	gettoken types 0 : 0
	gettoken type 0 : 0, parse("=")
	gettoken eqsign 0 : 0, parse("=")
	if `"`eqsign'"' != "=" { 
		exit
	}

	local chk = trim(`"`type'"')
	local l = length(`"`chk'"')

	if substr("weight",1,`l')==`"`chk'"' {
		local valid 1
	}
	else if substr("fweight",1,max(2,`l'))==`"`chk'"' {
		local valid 1
	}
	else if substr("aweight",1,max(2,`l'))==`"`chk'"' {
		local valid 1
	}
	else if substr("pweight",1,max(2,`l'))==`"`chk'"' {
		local valid 1
	}
	else if substr("iweight",1,max(2,`l'))==`"`chk'"' {
		local valid 1
	}
	else if substr("frequency",1,max(4,`l'))==`"`chk'"' {
		local valid 1
	}
	else if substr("cellsize",1,max(4,`l'))==`"`chk'"' {
		local valid 1
	}

	if "`valid'"=="" { exit }

	local nb 1
	while `nb' {
		gettoken subexp 0 : 0, parse(`""[]"') quotes
		if `"`subexp'"'=="]" {
			local nb = `nb' - 1
		}
		if `nb' {
			if `"`subexp'"'=="[" {
				local nb = `nb' + 1
			}
			local wexp `"`wexp'`subexp'"'
		}
	}
	sret local rest `"`0'"'
	local 0 `"[`type'=`wexp']"'
	syntax [`types']
	sret local weight `"[`weight'`exp']"'
	sret local done 1
end
exit

/*

   Syntax
		_parsewt "allowed_weight_types" command_stuff

		s(weight) = "[weight=exp]"

   Note: If there are weights, command must be less than 80 characters.

   Note: Program will issue the message "(frequency weights assumed)", etc.,
   if appropriate.

	version 6.0
	sret clear

	sret local newcmd "`*'"

program define StripWgt, sclass /* noclear  */
	version 6.0
	local nbrack "`1'"
	macro shift
	local cmdin "`*'"
	local i 1 
	while `i' < `nbrack' {
		local j = index("`cmdin'","[")
		local piece = substr("`cmdin'",1,`j')
		local cmdout "`cmdout'`piece'"
		local cmdin = substr("`cmdin'",`j'+1,.)
		local i = `i' + 1
	}
	local j = index("`cmdin'","[")
	local piece = substr("`cmdin'",1,`j'-1)
	local cmdout "`cmdout'`piece'"
	local cmdin = substr("`cmdin'",`j'+1,.)
	local j = index("`cmdin'","]")
	local piece = substr("`cmdin'",`j'+1,.)
	sret local newcmd "`cmdout'`piece'"
end
